cise, and persuasive.\n\nBy following these steps, you can ensure that your research proposal is well-thought-out, feasible, and ready for submission or further discussion.', 'agent3': 'Given the detailed analysis and the proposed research idea, the next logical step is to refine the research proposal and ensure that it aligns with your specific expertise and interests. Here are the next steps you can take:\n\n1. **Refine the Research Proposal:**\n   - Ensure that the research idea aligns with your focus on interpretability, efficiency, and societal impact.\n   - Incorporate your expertise in deep learning, time series forecasting, and ethical AI.\n\n2. **Develop a Detailed Methodology:**\n   - Specify the deep learning models and techniques you will use.\n   - Detail the datasets you will employ and how you will preprocess them.\n   - Outline the evaluation metrics and benchmarks you will use to assess the performance of your method.\n\n3. **Literature Review:**\n   - Conduct a thorough literature review to identify any recent advancements or gaps that your research can address.\n   - Ensure that your proposal is well-grounded in existing research.\n\n4. **Preliminary Experiments:**\n   - Conduct preliminary experiments to validate your approach.\n   - Use these results to refine your methodology and address any initial challenges.\n\n5. **Draft the Research Paper:**\n   - Start drafting the research paper based on the refined proposal.\n   - Include sections such as Introduction, Related Work, Methodology, Experiments, Results, and Conclusion.\n\n6. **Seek Feedback:**\n   - Share your draft with peers or mentors for feedback.\n   - Use their feedback to further refine your proposal and paper.\n\nGiven these steps, the next specific task could be to **refine the research proposal** by incorporating your specific expertise and ensuring it aligns with your goals. Here’s a more detailed breakdown of the next task:\n\n### Next Task: Refine the Research Proposal\n\n**Ob